com.navis.framework.portal.extensions

Class MobileTwoFieldSortDomainQueryContext

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.navis.framework.portal.extensions.MobileTwoFieldSortDomainQueryContext
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IMobileTwoFieldSortDomainQueryContext

    public class MobileTwoFieldSortDomainQueryContext
extends java.lang.Object
implements IMobileTwoFieldSortDomainQueryContext
    This object encapsulates the information necessary for performing a two field sort of a domain query. The information encapsulated is. - The first field to sort (MetafieldId). - The second column to sort (MetafieldId). - The sort direction of the first field (ascending / descending). - The sort direction of the second field (ascending / descending). This object also contains additional fields that will be added to the domain query before it is executed, and will also contain the domain query after it has been executed. This is passed through the Finder API (e.g., UnitFinder) when building a result list for a query so the query can be enhanced by the caller, and so the query is available to the caller. As is, the finder returns the result and not the query. The DomainQuery will be null until after the query has been executed.
    Author:
    Amos Parlante

                                            boolean inIsSecondSortInAscendingOrder)
        This construction allows all of the state to be populated at once during construciton. There are also seter methods so this class is not immutable.
        Parameters:
        inVariformId - The variform ID of the table this query provider is being applied to.
        inMobileFirstField - The mobile first metafield in the sort; this is the metatifeld in defining the mobile column.
        inEntityFirstField - The entity first metafield in the sort; this is the metafield backing the entity (can be null).
        inIsFirstSortInAscendingOrder - The sort order of the first field.
        inMobileSecondField - The mobile second metafield in the sort; this is the metatifeld in defining the mobile column.
        inEntitySecondField - The entity second metafield in the sort; this is the metafield backing the entity (can be null).
        inIsSecondSortInAscendingOrder - The sort order of the second field.

      • getDomainQueryResultLastExecuted

        @Nullable
public QueryResult getDomainQueryResultLastExecuted()
        This method returns the last domain query that was configured by this context. This method can return null when no domain query has been executed against this contxt yet. This is not a generic method that Carina can handle so product code will need to be done for the various mobile programs if this pattern is needed. It was added to the mobile reefer so that can be used as an example.
